
** To run this package you need a few things.

1. The GnuPG package.

$ apt-get install gnupg

2. The gnupg package for PHP (http://pecl.php.net/package/gnupg):

$ apt-get install php5-dev        # for making extensions
$ apt-get install php-pear        # provides pecl
$ apt-get install libgpgme11-dev  # the GNUPG Made Easy library.
$ pecl install gnupg
$ echo extension=gnupg.so >> $PHP_CONFIG/php.ini

3. The http package for PHP

$ apt-get install libcurl3-dev    # or mabye libcurl4-dev
$ pecl install pecl_http
$ echo extension=http.so >> $PHP_CONFIG/php.ini


** To initialize a new home page you will need to know its public URI. 
   Then run the init.sh script. GPG key generation can take some time.
   To speed it up use the mouse, keyboard or disk.


** To look at the keyring of the current installation:

$ export GNUPGHOME=./gnupghome
$ gpg --list-keys
